In[]:
**Data preprocessing**

The preprocessing involved reshaping the dataset and augmenting the training data using TensorFlow's ImageDataGenerator. This augmentation 
included random rotations, shifts, shears, zooms, flips, and rescaling, which helps the model generalize better by presenting varied
versions of the training images.

Building the model

** Developing an experimental network for the classification of dogs verses cats **

In[]:
A pre-trained MobileNetV2 model excluding the top layer was used as a base. The base layers were frozen to prevent their weights from being
updated during training, which is a common practice when using transfer learning to take advantage of previously learned patterns.
    
A new top layer, specifically a GlobalAveragePooling2D layer followed by a Dense layer with a sigmoid activation function, was added to 
perform binary classification (dog vs. cat). The model was compiled with the Adam optimizer and a learning rate of 0.0001, using binary
cross-entropy as the loss function.

import numpy as np
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import layers, models
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
from tensorflow.keras.applications import MobileNetV2
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix

# Paths to your data directories
train_dir = "/Users/palanchasushma/Documents/Advanced Machine Learning/AML ASSIGNMENT 3/Data/Train"
test_dir = "/Users/palanchasushma/Documents/Advanced Machine Learning/AML ASSIGNMENT 3/Data/Test"

# Initialize ImageDataGenerator with data augmentation for the training dataset
train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1./255,
    rotation_range=20,
    width_shift_range=0.1,
    height_shift_range=0.1,
    shear_range=0.1,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    fill_mode='nearest',
    validation_split=0.3333  # Validation split
)

test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255)  # Only rescaling for test data

# Load images from directories
train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    train_dir,
    target_size=(160, 160),  # Adjusted to match MobileNetV2 default
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary',  # Use 'categorical' for more than 2 classes
    subset='training'
)

validation_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    train_dir,
    target_size=(160, 160),  # Adjusted to match MobileNetV2 default
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary',
    subset='validation'
)

# Load the MobileNetV2 model pre-trained on ImageNet data but exclude the top (classification) layer
base_model = MobileNetV2(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(160, 160, 3))

# Freeze the base model layers to not train them
base_model.trainable = False

# Define the model
model = models.Sequential([
    base_model,
    layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(),
    layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')  # Use 'softmax' for categorical
])

# Compile the model with the corrected learning_rate parameter
model.compile(optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.0001),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

# Fit the model for 15 epochs
history = model.fit(
    train_generator,
    steps_per_epoch=train_generator.samples // train_generator.batch_size,
    epochs=15,
    validation_data=validation_generator,
    validation_steps=validation_generator.samples // validation_generator.batch_size
)

# Plotting training and validation accuracy and loss
acc = history.history['accuracy']
val_acc = history.history['val_accuracy']
loss = history.history['loss']
val_loss = history.history['val_loss']

epochs_range = range(len(acc))

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(epochs_range, acc, label='Training Accuracy')
plt.plot(epochs_range, val_acc, label='Validation Accuracy')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.title('Training and Validation Accuracy')

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.plot(epochs_range, loss, label='Training Loss')
plt.plot(epochs_range, val_loss, label='Validation Loss')
plt.legend(loc='upper right')
plt.title('Training and Validation Loss')
plt.show()

from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
import numpy as np
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix

# Initialize the test data generator
test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255)

# Assuming test_dir is your test dataset directory
test_generator = test_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    test_dir,
    target_size=(160, 160),  # Should match the training input size
    batch_size=32,  # Can adjust based on your memory constraints
    class_mode='binary',  # Use 'binary' for binary classification
    shuffle=False  # Important for correct label ordering
)

# Evaluate the model on the test dataset
test_loss, test_accuracy = model.evaluate(test_generator)
print(f'Test accuracy: {test_accuracy}, Test loss: {test_loss}')

# Predict on the test dataset
test_generator.reset()  # Resetting the generator to ensure correct order of predictions
predictions = model.predict(test_generator)

# For binary classification with 'sigmoid', threshold predictions at 0.5
y_pred = (predictions > 0.5).astype(int).flatten()
y_true = test_generator.classes  # True labels

# Calculate and print confusion matrix
conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)
print('Confusion Matrix:')
print(conf_matrix)

# Print classification report (precision, recall, f1-score)
print('Classification Report:')
print(classification_report(y_true, y_pred, target_names=test_generator.class_indices.keys()))

# Calculate correct and incorrect predictions
correct_predictions = sum(y_pred == y_true)
incorrect_predictions = sum(y_pred != y_true)
print(f'Correct predictions: {correct_predictions}')
print(f'Incorrect predictions: {incorrect_predictions}')

import numpy as np
import tensorflow as tf

from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
from tensorflow.keras.applications import MobileNetV2
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix

# Paths to your data directories
train_dir = "/Users/palanchasushma/Documents/Advanced Machine Learning/AML ASSIGNMENT 3/Data 2/Train"
test_dir = "/Users/palanchasushma/Documents/Advanced Machine Learning/AML ASSIGNMENT 3/Data 2/Test"

# Initialize ImageDataGenerator with data augmentation for the training dataset
train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1./255,
    rotation_range=20,
    width_shift_range=0.1,
    height_shift_range=0.1,
    shear_range=0.1,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    fill_mode='nearest',
    validation_split=0.2941  # Validation split
)

test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255)  # Only rescaling for test data

# Load images from directories
train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    train_dir,
    target_size=(160, 160),  # Adjusted to match MobileNetV2 default
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary',  # Use 'categorical' for more than 2 classes
    subset='training'
)

validation_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    train_dir,
    target_size=(160, 160),  # Adjusted to match MobileNetV2 default
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary',
    subset='validation'
)

# Load the MobileNetV2 model pre-trained on ImageNet data but exclude the top (classification) layer
base_model = MobileNetV2(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(160, 160, 3))

# Freeze the base model layers to not train them
base_model.trainable = False

# Define the model
model = models.Sequential([
    base_model,
    layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(),
    layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')  # Use 'softmax' for categorical
])

# Compile the model with the corrected learning_rate parameter
model.compile(optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.0001),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

# Fit the model for 15 epochs
history = model.fit(
    train_generator,
    steps_per_epoch=train_generator.samples // train_generator.batch_size,
    epochs=15,
    validation_data=validation_generator,
    validation_steps=validation_generator.samples // validation_generator.batch_size
)

plt.title('Training and Validation Accuracy')

plt.title('Training and Validation Loss')
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.applications import VGG16
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, GlobalAveragePooling2D, Dropout
from tensorflow.keras.models import Model
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import RMSprop
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping, ModelCheckpoint, ReduceLROnPlateau

# Define paths
train_dir = "/Users/palanchasushma/Documents/Advanced Machine Learning/AML ASSIGNMENT 3/Data/Train"
test_dir = "/Users/palanchasushma/Documents/Advanced Machine Learning/AML ASSIGNMENT 3/Data/Test"

# Data augmentation for training data
train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1./255,
    rotation_range=30,
    width_shift_range=0.2,
    height_shift_range=0.2,
    shear_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    validation_split=0.3333  # Split for validation
)

# Only rescaling for test data
test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255)

# Flow from directory for training and validation data
train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    train_dir,
    target_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary',
    subset='training'
)

validation_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    train_dir,
    target_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary',
    subset='validation'
)

# Load VGG16 base model without the top layer
base_model = VGG16(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(224, 224, 3))

# Freeze the layers of the base model
base_model.trainable = False

# Adding custom layers on top of VGG16 base
x = base_model.output
x = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(x)
x = Dense(512, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dropout(0.5)(x)  # Dropout for regularization
predictions = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)

model = Model(inputs=base_model.input, outputs=predictions)

# Compile the model
model.compile(optimizer=RMSprop(learning_rate=1e-4),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

# Callbacks
early_stopping = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, mode='min')
model_checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint(filepath='best_model.keras', save_best_only=True, monitor='val_loss', mode='min')
reduce_lr = ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.2, patience=5, verbose=1, mode='min', min_lr=1e-6)

# Train the model
history = model.fit(
    train_generator,
    steps_per_epoch=train_generator.samples // train_generator.batch_size,
    epochs=20,
    validation_data=validation_generator,
    validation_steps=validation_generator.samples // validation_generator.batch_size,
    callbacks=[early_stopping, model_checkpoint, reduce_lr]
)

# Load the best model
model = tf.keras.models.load_model('best_model.keras')

# Prepare test data generator
test_generator = test_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    test_dir,
    target_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary'
)

# Evaluate the model on test data
test_loss, test_accuracy = model.evaluate(test_generator)
print(f'Test accuracy: {test_accuracy:.3f}, Test loss: {test_loss:.3f}')

# Plotting training/validation accuracy and loss
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], label='Training Accuracy')
plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], label='Validation Accuracy')
plt.title('Accuracy over epochs')
plt.legend()

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.plot(history.history['loss'], label='Training Loss')
plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'], label='Validation Loss')
plt.title('Loss over epochs')
plt.legend()

plt.show()

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.applications import VGG16
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, GlobalAveragePooling2D, Dropout
from tensorflow.keras.models import Model
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import RMSprop
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping, ModelCheckpoint, ReduceLROnPlateau

# Define paths
train_dir = "/Users/palanchasushma/Documents/Advanced Machine Learning/AML ASSIGNMENT 3/Data 1/Train"
test_dir = "/Users/palanchasushma/Documents/Advanced Machine Learning/AML ASSIGNMENT 3/Data 1/Test"

# Data augmentation for training data
train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1./255,
    rotation_range=20,
    width_shift_range=0.2,
    height_shift_range=0.2,
    shear_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    validation_split=0.25  # Split for validation
)

# Only rescaling for test data
test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255)

# Flow from directory for training and validation data
train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    train_dir,
    target_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary',
    subset='training'
)

validation_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    train_dir,
    target_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary',
    subset='validation'
)

# Load VGG16 base model without the top layer
base_model = VGG16(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(224, 224, 3))

# Freeze the layers of the base model
base_model.trainable = False

# Adding custom layers on top of VGG16 base
x = base_model.output
x = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(x)
x = Dense(512, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dropout(0.5)(x)  # Dropout for regularization
predictions = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)

model = Model(inputs=base_model.input, outputs=predictions)

# Compile the model
model.compile(optimizer=RMSprop(learning_rate=1e-4),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

# Callbacks
early_stopping = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, mode='min')
model_checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint(filepath='best_model.keras', save_best_only=True, monitor='val_loss', mode='min')
reduce_lr = ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.2, patience=5, verbose=1, mode='min', min_lr=1e-6)

# Train the model
history = model.fit(
    train_generator,
    steps_per_epoch=train_generator.samples // train_generator.batch_size,
    epochs=20,
    validation_data=validation_generator,
    validation_steps=validation_generator.samples // validation_generator.batch_size,
    callbacks=[early_stopping, model_checkpoint, reduce_lr]
)

# Load the best model
model = tf.keras.models.load_model('best_model.keras')

# Prepare test data generator
test_generator = test_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    test_dir,
    target_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary'
)

# Evaluate the model on test data
test_loss, test_accuracy = model.evaluate(test_generator)
print(f'Test accuracy: {test_accuracy:.3f}, Test loss: {test_loss:.3f}')

# Plotting training/validation accuracy and loss
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], label='Training Accuracy')
plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], label='Validation Accuracy')
plt.title('Accuracy over epochs')
plt.legend()

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.plot(history.history['loss'], label='Training Loss')
plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'], label='Validation Loss')
plt.title('Loss over epochs')
plt.legend()

plt.show()

# Define paths

test_dir = "/Users/palanchasushma/Documents/Advanced Machine Learning/AML ASSIGNMENT 3/Data 2/Test"

# Data augmentation for training data

    rescale=1./255,
    rotation_range=20,
    width_shift_range=0.2,
    height_shift_range=0.2,
    shear_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,

)

# Only rescaling for test data
test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255)

# Flow from directory for training and validation data
train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    train_dir,
    target_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary',
    subset='training'
)

validation_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    train_dir,
    target_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary',
    subset='validation'
)

# Load VGG16 base model without the top layer
base_model = VGG16(weights='imagenet', include_top=False, input_shape=(224, 224, 3))

# Freeze the layers of the base model
base_model.trainable = False

# Adding custom layers on top of VGG16 base
x = base_model.output
x = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(x)
x = Dense(512, activation='relu')(x)
x = Dropout(0.5)(x)  # Dropout for regularization
predictions = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)

model = Model(inputs=base_model.input, outputs=predictions)

# Compile the model
model.compile(optimizer=RMSprop(learning_rate=1e-4),
              loss='binary_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

# Callbacks
early_stopping = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, verbose=1, mode='min')
model_checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint(filepath='best_model.keras', save_best_only=True, monitor='val_loss', mode='min')
reduce_lr = ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.2, patience=5, verbose=1, mode='min', min_lr=1e-6)

# Train the model
history = model.fit(
    train_generator,
    steps_per_epoch=train_generator.samples // train_generator.batch_size,
    epochs=20,
    validation_data=validation_generator,
    validation_steps=validation_generator.samples // validation_generator.batch_size,
    callbacks=[early_stopping, model_checkpoint, reduce_lr]
)

# Load the best model
model = tf.keras.models.load_model('best_model.keras')

# Prepare test data generator
test_generator = test_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    test_dir,
    target_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='binary'
)

# Evaluate the model on test data
test_loss, test_accuracy = model.evaluate(test_generator)
print(f'Test accuracy: {test_accuracy:.3f}, Test loss: {test_loss:.3f}')

# Plotting training/validation accuracy and loss
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], label='Training Accuracy')
plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], label='Validation Accuracy')
plt.title('Accuracy over epochs')
plt.legend()

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.plot(history.history['loss'], label='Training Loss')
plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'], label='Validation Loss')
plt.title('Loss over epochs')
plt.legend()

plt.show()
